  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Walliserhof has recently undergone extensive renovations and is now ready to show you its new design and unique concept. The public areas have a modern alpine style which follow through to the individually decorated guest rooms.</p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>During your stay at the Walliserhof, you'll be positioned in the centre of the village and have easy access to the resort amenities, including a range of bars and restaurants. You'll also have free use of the hotel shuttle service to the slopes during it's operating hours and the public ski bus stop is located just outside the building. If you would prefer to walk, the closest ski lifts are located a short 5 minutes' walk from the hotel.</p>
<h2>After ski relaxation</h2>
<p>Be sure to check out the superb 2,100m² spa complete with swimming pool, var<span>ious saunas, a steam bath, a whirlpool and a light-flooded relaxation area. If you fancy some pampering, the wellness experts offer a long menu of massages and cosmetic treatments. </span><span>Talking of menus, dine around in the hotels three restaurants, Cäsar Ritz, Del Ponte Pizzeria and Fondue-Stübli - There's plenty of choice when it comes to your evening meal.</span></p>
<h2><span>Last Christmas</span></h2>
<p><span>Saas Fee celebrates 40 years of Wham!'s Last Christmas music video being shot in the village, and as the crew and George Michael stayed at the Walliserhof, they too are reviving the memories of when the team stayed there in 1984. Throughout December there is live music with DJ sets every Friday &amp; Saturday, and on the 21st December 2024 you can celebrate Wham! at the Last Christmas's Big 40th Birthday Party. While you're there take part in a augmented reality scavenger hunt through the hotel to 'find the missing props for the music video' with a George Michael cocktail - it costs CHF10 and includes a cocktail.</span></p>
<h2><span>Family friendly</span></h2>
<p><span>If you have children over the age of two, take advantage of the free supervised play room service to allow you to enjoy the spa in the afternoon or a drink or meal a bit later on. Families are also well catered for as the Walliserhof offers early meal times for children in the restaurant and facilities such as cots free of charge. </span></p>
<h3>Why is this an Inghams' Choice property?</h3>
<p><strong>Central location</strong>-  With an excellent position in Saas Fee, the resort centre and ski lifts are just a short walk away.</p>
<p><strong>Sit back and relax</strong> - With an extensive spa area, the Walliserhof Grand Hotel &amp; Spa is the best choice if you want somewhere you can truly relax after a day on the slopes. </p>
<p><strong>Tasty food </strong>- <span> With three on-site restaurants you are truly spoilt for choice. Meals are taken in the gourmet Cäsar Ritz and Del Pointe, both serving tasty dishes from a seasonal menu.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
